An **Australian mortgage calculator** estimates your monthly and fortnightly home loan repayments, total interest payable over the loan life, and total amount repaid. Enter your loan amount, interest rate, and loan term to see a full repayment breakdown.

As of May 2026, the average Australian variable home loan rate is approximately **6.3% per annum**, with the RBA cash rate at 4.10%. Repayments on a $600,000 loan over 30 years at 6.3% are approximately $3,718 per month. Switching to fortnightly repayments can save over $70,000 in interest over the life of the loan.
